Halve the @bell pepper{1} and @green pepper{1} and remove the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Drain the @firm tofu{280%g}, dry with #kitchen paper{} and chop into roughly 2cm cubes. Roughly chop the @coriander{1} (stalks and all). Zest the @lime{1} then chop into wedges.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} or #wok{} over medium-high heat. Add the tofu and peppers. Stir-fry, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Lower the heat slightly and stir in the @sweet chilli sauce{64%g} and @soy sauce{50%g}. Stir-fry for another ~{2-3%minutes} until the peppers are just soft.

Meanwhile, cook the @steamed basmati rice{1} according to pack instructions.

Stir the lime zest, half the coriander and half the @salted peanuts{25%g} through the stir-fry.

Serve the rice in #bowls{} topped with the veggie tofu stir-fry. Finish with a scattering of the remaining coriander and peanuts and the lime wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!